  "issues": [
    {
      "number": 3,
      "id": "I_kwDOSaLcns8AAAABC1DSNw",
      "title": "Commits delivery using GSA_REKEY",
      "url": "https://github.com/kkohbrok/draft-kohbrok-ipsecme-mls-gike/issues/3",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "smyslov",
      "authorAssociation": "NONE",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "For scalability reasons, it would be desirable to re-use GSA_REKEY pseudo-exchange to fan out MLS commits.",
      "createdAt": "2026-05-20T08:56:32Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-20T08:56:32Z",
      "closedAt": null,
      "comments": []
    },
    {
      "number": 5,
      "id": "I_kwDOSaLcns8AAAABDZDhQQ",
      "title": "Make only group senders responsible for creating MLS commits",
      "url": "https://github.com/kkohbrok/draft-kohbrok-ipsecme-mls-gike/issues/5",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "smyslov",
      "authorAssociation": "NONE",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "Currently any GM can be used by the GCKS to ask for MLS commits. I think that this should be limited to group senders only.\nRequesting commits requites a unicast IKE SA between the GCKS and a GM. RFC 9838 already proposes that in large groups with small number of senders (e.g. live broadcast) the GCKS can maintain unicast IKE SA to senders and use multicast GSA_REKEY to deliver updates to receivers. This ensures that no interruption of traffic happens if network is lossy - update to senders is reliable.\n",
      "createdAt": "2026-05-26T08:10:49Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-26T08:10:49Z",
      "closedAt": null,
      "comments": []
    },
    {
      "number": 6,
      "id": "I_kwDOSaLcns8AAAABDZFYTQ",
      "title": "Re-use existing G-IKEv2 registries for MLS objects",
      "url": "https://github.com/kkohbrok/draft-kohbrok-ipsecme-mls-gike/issues/6",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "smyslov",
      "authorAssociation": "NONE",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "Currently the draft uses the only new G-IKEv2 attribute mls_commit` object for wrapping all MLS objects. THe type of MLS object is determined by additional value MlsGikeObjectType inside this attribute. This would require creating a new IANA registry to manage these types. Instead, we can use the existing IANA registries for G-IKEv2 attributes and allocate a separate attribute for each MLS object.",
      "createdAt": "2026-05-26T08:15:37Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-26T08:15:37Z",
      "closedAt": null,
      "comments": []
    }
  ],
