    {
      "number": 4,
      "id": "PR_kwDOSaLcns7d0adT",
      "title": "Multicast GSA_REKEY with optional LKH protection",
      "url": "https://github.com/kkohbrok/draft-kohbrok-ipsecme-mls-gike/pull/4",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "kkohbrok",
      "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "Fixes #3 ",
      "createdAt": "2026-05-21T06:32:30Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-21T14:14:12Z",
      "baseRepository": "kkohbrok/draft-kohbrok-ipsecme-mls-gike",
      "baseRefName": "konrad/fewer_payloads",
      "baseRefOid": "7f2a44c5097de760bcca268c24b70fe5d7ca55e2",
      "headRepository": "kkohbrok/draft-kohbrok-ipsecme-mls-gike",
      "headRefName": "konrad/lkh_for_rekey_multicast",
      "headRefOid": "3a6cd85233b5ddca2f258b278fc1b80cd5f363fd",
      "closedAt": null,
      "mergedAt": null,
      "mergedBy": null,
      "mergeCommit": null,
      "comments": [],
      "reviews": [
        {
          "id": "PRR_kwDOSaLcns8AAAABAog6JA",
          "commit": {
            "abbreviatedOid": "3a6cd85"
          },
          "author": "smyslov",
          "authorAssociation": "NONE",
          "state": "COMMENTED",
          "body": "",
          "createdAt": "2026-05-21T13:46:24Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-05-21T13:46:24Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 18,
              "body": "For multicast fan out using GSA_REKEY, AUTH_KEY is needed. It contains a GCKS's public key, that is provided to a GM at the time of registration, so that when multicast rekey message is received, the GM can verify its signature.\nIn addition, WRAP_KEY attributes are needed for LKH. They contain the path (a sequence of keys when each next is encrypted, or wrapped, with the previous) in the logical key tree for a GM. This path in a tree is specific for each GM (as they are leafs in the tree), so later the GCKS can craft a message that, while being received by all GMs, would not be possible to decrypt for the excluded GM.",
              "createdAt": "2026-05-21T13:46:24Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-05-21T13:46:24Z"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PRR_kwDOSaLcns8AAAABAokVdg",
          "commit": {
            "abbreviatedOid": "3a6cd85"
          },
          "author": "smyslov",
          "authorAssociation": "NONE",
          "state": "COMMENTED",
          "body": "",
          "createdAt": "2026-05-21T13:52:46Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-05-21T13:52:47Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 78,
              "body": "The GCKS first rekeys the REkey SA itseld using LKH, thus leaving the excluded GM an ability to decrypt multicast messages on new Rekey SA. Then it can fan-out MLS objects installing new Data-security SA using a new Rekey SA. The excluded GM will be able to see this message, but unable to decrypt it. Just for clarification.",
              "createdAt": "2026-05-21T13:52:47Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-05-21T14:09:37Z"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PRR_kwDOSaLcns8AAAABAol-Ow",
          "commit": {
            "abbreviatedOid": "3a6cd85"
          },
          "author": "smyslov",
          "authorAssociation": "NONE",
          "state": "COMMENTED",
          "body": "",
          "createdAt": "2026-05-21T13:55:31Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-05-21T13:55:31Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 110,
              "body": "I think this is true even if GSA_REKEY is not used :-)",
              "createdAt": "2026-05-21T13:55:31Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-05-21T13:55:31Z"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PRR_kwDOSaLcns8AAAABAooF6g",
          "commit": {
            "abbreviatedOid": "3a6cd85"
          },
          "author": "smyslov",
          "authorAssociation": "NONE",
          "state": "COMMENTED",
          "body": "",
          "createdAt": "2026-05-21T13:59:25Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-05-21T13:59:26Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 112,
              "body": "AUTH_KEY and WRAP_KEY are Member Key Bag attributes. And they are needed for multicast GSA_REKEY (WRAP_KEY - in case of LKH).",
              "createdAt": "2026-05-21T13:59:26Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-05-21T13:59:34Z"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PRR_kwDOSaLcns8AAAABAot2jw",
          "commit": {
            "abbreviatedOid": "3a6cd85"
          },
          "author": "smyslov",
          "authorAssociation": "NONE",
          "state": "COMMENTED",
          "body": "",
          "createdAt": "2026-05-21T14:11:01Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-05-21T14:11:01Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 146,
              "body": "This should be 2-staged: first rekey the Rekey SA (and exclude a GM) and then distribute the MLS objects. Thus, 2 messages must be depicted.",
              "createdAt": "2026-05-21T14:11:01Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-05-21T14:11:01Z"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "PRR_kwDOSaLcns8AAAABAovarA",
          "commit": {
            "abbreviatedOid": "3a6cd85"
          },
          "author": "smyslov",
          "authorAssociation": "NONE",
          "state": "COMMENTED",
          "body": "",
          "createdAt": "2026-05-21T14:14:12Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-05-21T14:14:12Z",
          "comments": [
            {
              "originalPosition": 154,
              "body": "True, but needs clarification. The Rekey SA keys are always generated and provided exclusively by the GCKS (as well as all wrap keys for LKH). This is from G-IKEv2 and is not changed. The second part is obvious and does not depend on whether multicast rekey or inband rekey is used.",
              "createdAt": "2026-05-21T14:14:12Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-05-21T14:14:12Z"
            }
          ]
        }
